{
  "texts": [
    "Following 6 weeks of exercise, the results showed that the HIIT group demonstrated greater improvements compared to MICT in waist circumference (∆ m2-m1% HIIT 4.1%, p = 0.002 vs. ∆ m2-m1% MICT 2.5%, p = 0.002) and body fat mass (∆ m2-m1% HIIT 4.5%, p < 0.001 vs. ∆ m2-m1% MICT 3.2%, p < 0.001).",
    "The control group had no improvements; on the other hand, all values of body composition measurements increased over time.",
    "These results were only maintained at 6 months of follow-up in the HIIT group, which demonstrated a significant decreasing trend in waist circumference (∆ m3-m2% -2 cm, p = 0.033) compared to MICT (p = 0.016) and Control (p = 0.001), and maintained at 12 months of follow-up with significant differences to MICT (p = 0.018) and control (p = 0.001).",
    "There were also significant differences in body fat at 6 months in the HIIT group compared to the MICT (p = 0.05) and control (p = 0.047) groups, as well as at 12 months compared to MICT (p = 0.",
    "Following the 6 weeks of supervised program, aerobic capacity significantly increased by 14% with HIIT (Δ m2-m1 2.5 ± 1.5 ml kg -1 min -1, p < 0.001) and 9% with MICT (Δ m2-m1 1.4 ± 1.2 ml kg -1 min -1, p < 0.001) (Fig. 4)."
  ]
}